cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically crowd counting. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network structure that integrates multi-scale features and auxiliary tasks, which involves machine learning techniques such as graph neural networks and joint reasoning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques for improving accuracy, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on four datasets, which involves multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
